rComments: Before I took this class, I didn't know what a vector was. However, Professor Christie was very helpful, and his practice exams were always similar to his tests! Not to mention, he always posts his notes online, which is very helpful. Lastly, he was very attentive towards his students, and would answer your question in the lecture itself or outside

Great proff. All the class notes, assignments, and practice exams are on his personal website which makes it very easy to follow along. Great grading scheme with a DGD exam every two weeks on only a few sections per exam. Follow along with the class notes and you will pass.

He definitely know everything in his class. However, he just don't know how to express it by words clearly. He talks in very soft voice, and he talks when he is writing, this makes his class super case and I don't even have time to understand all the materials.

Overall, he's not a bad prof. For 1302, he posts all notes online, which is great because you can miss class, read the notes, and still get a good grade. He's also young and hipster but he doesn't interact with the class to much beyond the course material. He's very helpful during his office hours.

He's a really nice guy who seems to really care about the class. He's helpful and approachable when you ask a question in person. However, he needs to improve his teaching style! He has little eye contact with the class and his teaching is pretty monotone and boring. He's young so he should take advantage of that to better connect with students.

He is probably a nice guy, but he is new to teaching so he talks really fast and his voice is really low and not easily understandable. He posts note online which are really helpful. If you can choose a better prof, go for it.

He's new to teaching (very obvious. I understood the material but had NO IDEA what he was saying in class. All over the place. Constantly corrects himself or is corrected by students. However, he does seem like he genuinely cares about his students

He's clearly new to teaching, and I wasn't a big fan to begin with, as he seemed flustered. As the term went on, I felt that he actually became a very good teacher. I'm glad that he'll be my prof for MAT1302 next term, as his course requirements are quite straightforward. Also, don't hesitate to ask questions, as he's more than happy to answer them
New professor, so naturally a couple hiccups here and there.  Very clear, and wants you to succeed.  Endorses asking questions, and really loves what he teaches.  This guy will go far.
